{
  "number": 3148,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3148",
  "title": "Unmount using routing",
  "body": "When unmounting some widget that requires a configuration in a context of an app that leverages the routing we have an error.\r\n\r\nMore specifically it happens on those widgets:\r\n - [toggle](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=Toggle.default)\r\n - [starRating](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=StarRating.default)\r\n - [menu](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?widgets=unmount&selectedStory=Menu.default)\r\n\r\nTo reproduce just mount and remount.\r\n\r\nI've tested with a modified dev-novel that doesn't use the routing manager and it works fine. Also the stack trace indicates that the error happens during the routingManager lifecycle (addWidgets).\r\n\r\n<img width=\"909\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-09-25 at 15 14 10\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/393765/46016673-ae525b00-c0d5-11e8-9e50-7845b84e1163.png\">\r\n\r\nThose widgets have in common that they try to set a value or get information about a facet that is not defined in the search state. If the router widget was always called last we wouldn't have this issue.",
